This paper discusses the use of natural processes for intelligent functionalities, specifically using single photons for reinforcement learning and decision making. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), and programming languages (cs.PL). However, given the focus on reinforcement learning and decision making, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The use of hierarchical architecture also suggests a potential connection to cs.SY.
